eriods": true, "protocol": "https", "resolution": "720x1280", "aspect_ratio": 0.56, "filesize_approx": 17051006, "http_headers": {"User-Agent": "Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 10.0; Win64; x64) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/97.0.4692.20 Safari/537.36", "Accept": "text/html,application/xhtml+xml,application/xml;q=0.9,*/*;q=0.8", "Accept-Language": "en-us,en;q=0.5", "Sec-Fetch-Mode": "navigate", "Referer": "https://www.instagram.com/"}, "video_ext": "mp4", "audio_ext": "none", "abr": 0, "vbr": 974.559, "format": "dash-1588890805558083v - 720x1280 (DASH video)"}], "title": "Video by gigaqian", "description": "Quantum computing is basically about processing information simultaneously. That said, we’re playing with numerous unknowns and the main technology has been kept from the public. Origin Pilot is the first major step towards changing that in a meaningful way. It’s important to note that parts of this video oversimplify concepts to make them digestible. For instance, observing quantum entanglement typically breaks the entanglement - it’s more about the identification of the phenomenon that is so “spooky” and fascinating.\n#quantumcomputing #tech #learn #chinesetech #gigaqian", "duration": 139.969, "timestamp": 1772852281, "uploader_id": "70561211886", "uploader": "Giga Qian", "channel": "gigaqian", "like_count": 17415, "comment_count": 580, "comments": [{"author": "p2_development_group_arizona_", "author_id": "77377305188", "id": "18313165450287563", "text": "", "timestamp": 1775354809}, {"author": "p2_development_group_arizona_", "author_id": "77377305188", "id": "18111727615840195", "text": "I'm a Forensic Architectural & Building\nConsultant and Public\nAdjuster operating through\nM&M Adjusters and my forensic division, MFAD\n(Mann Forensics Analyst Division). My work focuses on reconstructing complex property insurance claims by integrating causation analysis, structured evidence systems, and policy-aligned valuation modeling.\nFrom a systems perspective, what I do is take\nunstructured, incomplete, and often conflicting datasets-including meteorological data, field observations, photographic evidence, and policy language-and convert them into a coherent, defensible claim architecture.\n\nYesterday after going through everything I had been constructing for nearly 6hrs, I'm transitioning away from ChatGPT following a drift issue that introduced risk across roughly $7M in active claim exposure.\nI need a platform that offers tighter control, consistency, and better workflow management.\nWhat's your recommendation for migrating my existing ChatGPT history and\nintegrating into a more stable\nAl system?", "timestamp": 1775354787}, {"author": "kerwoodjim", "author_id": "27479232680", "id": "17873211054575805", "text": "If you know the position of the bit on earth you know the position on the one on the moon.  You cannot set the bit.", "timestamp": 1775228030}, {"author": "ketrolee", "author_id": "7344893868", "id": "18077001143439018", "text": "I really need to get smarter.", "timestamp": 1775227753}, {"author": "consciouscuppa", "author_id": "76538520068", "id": "18110519005768350", "text": "It's so exciting but remember, we are doing even faster calculations and manifestations in real time of our whole environment, people and emotions and thoughts", "timestamp": 1775207841}, {"author": "lovinthehilife", "author_id": "385983266", "id": "18576821317048157", "text": "If it’s so good, why isn’t anyone using it to solve hashtag puzzles?", "timestamp": 1775204421}, {"author": "juniorlopez1960", "author_id": "2096824215", "id": "18083109725062634", "text": "Amen Amen Amen Thank You Jesus", "timestamp": 1775126703}, {"author": "johnwrites51", "author_id": "60543190907", "id": "18092509442156851", "text": "....so how many realities can we have at once???", "timestamp": 1774977529}, {"author": "jfjton", "author_id": "1222995549", "id": "17986304879971049", "text": "So how do we know an answer is correct once we observe it?", "